This paper is about routing in wireless multihop networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of transmission rates and optimization algorithms, which are topics that fall under information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS), respectively. The paper presents polynomial-time algorithms for routing, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.SY, in that order.
